{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-js","path":"/reanimation","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>I am going through a course on <a href=\"https://courses.edx.org\">edx.org</a> named: <a href=\"https://courses.edx.org/courses/course-v1:HarvardX+MCB80.1x+3T2019/course/\">Fundamentals of Neuroscience, Part 1: The Electrical Properties of the Neuron</a>. Binge watching lecture series are not as effective as watching movie-series. To that extent I couldn't enjoy movie series at a stretch anyway. Interest alone can only take one so far. So I decided to take a break and watch a few <em>treats</em> hidden for the later parts of the course.</p>\n<p>I remember visiting <a href=\"https://backyardbrains.com/\">backyardbrains</a> looking for neuroscience experiments and found a bunch of tools, blogs, experiments that I wish I had found before. I see a video lecture from the same team that makes <a href=\"https://backyardbrains.com/products/\">these things</a>.</p>\n<p>This video session contained the following:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Getting a Cockroach unconscious.</li>\n<li>Obtaining artifacts.</li>\n<li>Rate coding the neural activity.</li>\n<li>Getting the leg to move.</li>\n</ol>\n<h2 id=\"prepare-the-subject\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#prepare-the-subject\" aria-label=\"prepare the subject permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Prepare the subject</h2>\n<p>Cockroaches are cold blooded animals. So from the Nernst Equation:</p>\n<span class=\"katex-display\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>E</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>R</mi><mi>T</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>z</mi><mi>F</mi></mrow></mfrac><mi>ln</mi><mo>⁡</mo><mfrac><mtext>ion concentration outside </mtext><mtext>ion concentration inside</mtext></mfrac></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">E = \\frac{RT}{zF}\\ln{\\frac{\\text{ion } \\text{concentration } \\text{outside }}{\\text{ion } \\text{concentration } \\text{inside}}}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.05764em;\">E</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:2.05744em;vertical-align:-0.686em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mopen nulldelimiter\"></span><span class=\"mfrac\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:1.36033em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.314em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.04398em;\">z</span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">F</span></span></span><span style=\"top:-3.23em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"frac-line\" style=\"border-bottom-width:0.04em;\"></span></span><span style=\"top:-3.677em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.00773em;\">R</span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">T</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.686em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mclose nulldelimiter\"></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.16666666666666666em;\"></span><span class=\"mop\">ln</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.16666666666666666em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mopen nulldelimiter\"></span><span class=\"mfrac\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:1.37144em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.314em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord text\"><span class=\"mord\">ion </span></span><span class=\"mord text\"><span class=\"mord\">concentration </span></span><span class=\"mord text\"><span class=\"mord\">inside</span></span></span></span><span style=\"top:-3.23em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"frac-line\" style=\"border-bottom-width:0.04em;\"></span></span><span style=\"top:-3.677em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord text\"><span class=\"mord\">ion </span></span><span class=\"mord text\"><span class=\"mord\">concentration </span></span><span class=\"mord text\"><span class=\"mord\">outside </span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.686em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mclose nulldelimiter\"></span></span></span></span></span></span></span>\n<p>We can tell that as the temperature falls, the electric field due to any ions will cease to exist. This is all that's needed to put the cockroach unconscious, a bucket full of ice-water.</p>\n<h2 id=\"obtaining-artifacts\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#obtaining-artifacts\" aria-label=\"obtaining artifacts permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Obtaining artifacts</h2>\n<p><figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 690px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/blog/static/e8d5b177024fcea4de51b431f5603e47/29d31/RoachwithLeg_web.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 122.54335260115607%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Credits - https://backyardbrains.com/experiments/spikerbox\"\n        title=\"Credits - https://backyardbrains.com/experiments/spikerbox\"\n        src=\"/blog/static/e8d5b177024fcea4de51b431f5603e47/15ec7/RoachwithLeg_web.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/blog/static/e8d5b177024fcea4de51b431f5603e47/9ac50/RoachwithLeg_web.jpg 173w,\n/blog/static/e8d5b177024fcea4de51b431f5603e47/8d48c/RoachwithLeg_web.jpg 345w,\n/blog/static/e8d5b177024fcea4de51b431f5603e47/15ec7/RoachwithLeg_web.jpg 690w,\n/blog/static/e8d5b177024fcea4de51b431f5603e47/29d31/RoachwithLeg_web.jpg 700w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 690px) 100vw, 690px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">Credits - https://backyardbrains.com/experiments/spikerbox</figcaption>\n  </figure></p>\n<p>Once you have an unconscious cockroach, you umm... are required to do the thing.</p>\n<h2 id=\"rate-coding-neural-activity\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#rate-coding-neural-activity\" aria-label=\"rate coding neural activity permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Rate coding neural activity</h2>\n<p>Place the leg on cork surface and pin two electrodes in, as shown in the image:\n<figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 600px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/blog/static/65bb17d1ae74658a877197bcd42f6436/b4294/legwithwires_web.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 79.76878612716763%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Credits - https://backyardbrains.com/experiments/spikerbox\"\n        title=\"Credits - https://backyardbrains.com/experiments/spikerbox\"\n        src=\"/blog/static/65bb17d1ae74658a877197bcd42f6436/b4294/legwithwires_web.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/blog/static/65bb17d1ae74658a877197bcd42f6436/9ac50/legwithwires_web.jpg 173w,\n/blog/static/65bb17d1ae74658a877197bcd42f6436/8d48c/legwithwires_web.jpg 345w,\n/blog/static/65bb17d1ae74658a877197bcd42f6436/b4294/legwithwires_web.jpg 600w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">Credits - https://backyardbrains.com/experiments/spikerbox</figcaption>\n  </figure>\nWe need a device to amplify the potential difference so that it can be seen while isolating noise. Touching the hairs of the leg causes neurons to spike and create a response that can be seen in the following image:</p>\n<p><figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 690px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/blog/static/61aab1b0d192e2812a4e7550138bde84/d924d/Exp1_exp05_spiketrain.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 32.369942196531795%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Credits - https://backyardbrains.com/experiments/spikerbox\"\n        title=\"Credits - https://backyardbrains.com/experiments/spikerbox\"\n        src=\"/blog/static/61aab1b0d192e2812a4e7550138bde84/15ec7/Exp1_exp05_spiketrain.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/blog/static/61aab1b0d192e2812a4e7550138bde84/9ac50/Exp1_exp05_spiketrain.jpg 173w,\n/blog/static/61aab1b0d192e2812a4e7550138bde84/8d48c/Exp1_exp05_spiketrain.jpg 345w,\n/blog/static/61aab1b0d192e2812a4e7550138bde84/15ec7/Exp1_exp05_spiketrain.jpg 690w,\n/blog/static/61aab1b0d192e2812a4e7550138bde84/af659/Exp1_exp05_spiketrain.jpg 1035w,\n/blog/static/61aab1b0d192e2812a4e7550138bde84/d924d/Exp1_exp05_spiketrain.jpg 1238w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 690px) 100vw, 690px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">Credits - https://backyardbrains.com/experiments/spikerbox</figcaption>\n  </figure></p>\n<p>Zooming into a section shows the action potential of a neuron. The reason behind this behaviour is stated to be the opening and closing of <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>N</mi><msup><mi>a</mi><mo lspace=\"0em\" rspace=\"0em\">+</mo></msup></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">Na^{+}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.771331em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.10903em;\">N</span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathdefault\">a</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.771331em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">+</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span>, <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msup><mi>K</mi><mo lspace=\"0em\" rspace=\"0em\">+</mo></msup></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{K}^{+}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.771331em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.07153em;\">K</span></span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.771331em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">+</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> ion-channels.</p>\n<p><figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 451px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/blog/static/95017fdecf50ee8a9854159b6fc1fc6c/b5072/Exp1_exp06_closeupspike.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 86.70520231213872%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Credits - https://backyardbrains.com/experiments/spikerbox\"\n        title=\"Credits - https://backyardbrains.com/experiments/spikerbox\"\n        src=\"/blog/static/95017fdecf50ee8a9854159b6fc1fc6c/b5072/Exp1_exp06_closeupspike.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/blog/static/95017fdecf50ee8a9854159b6fc1fc6c/9ac50/Exp1_exp06_closeupspike.jpg 173w,\n/blog/static/95017fdecf50ee8a9854159b6fc1fc6c/8d48c/Exp1_exp06_closeupspike.jpg 345w,\n/blog/static/95017fdecf50ee8a9854159b6fc1fc6c/b5072/Exp1_exp06_closeupspike.jpg 451w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 451px) 100vw, 451px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">Credits - https://backyardbrains.com/experiments/spikerbox</figcaption>\n  </figure></p>\n<h2 id=\"getting-the-leg-to-move\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#getting-the-leg-to-move\" aria-label=\"getting the leg to move permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Getting the leg to move</h2>\n<p>So far, we read the information that was going across the limb, reading the neural signals. Is it possible to send signals back? and what does that do?</p>\n<p>The course shares that a song with high <em>bass</em> component is a good fit because of the lower frequency in the audio that gets encoded as electricity would cause the leg to twitch. The twitching is inversely proportional to the frequency and directly proportional to the volume. Here's the video from backyardbrains.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-resp-iframe-wrapper\" style=\"padding-bottom: 56.25%; position: relative; height: 0; overflow: hidden; \" > <iframe src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/edEXKiOmPvE?start=720\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture\" allowfullscreen style=\" position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; width: 100%; height: 100%; \"></iframe> </div>\n<p><em>fin</em>.</p>","timeToRead":3,"excerpt":"I am going through a course on edx.org named: Fundamentals of Neuroscience, Part 1: The Electrical Properties of the Neuron. Binge watching…","frontmatter":{"title":"Reanimation","cover":"https://unsplash.it/1152/300/?random?BirchintheRoses","date":"2020-04-20T00:00:00.000Z","categories":["readings"],"tags":["neuroscience"]},"fields":{"slug":"/reanimation","date":"April 19, 2020"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/reanimation","nexttitle":"Regular expressions and efficiency","nextslug":"/regular-expressions-and-efficiency","prevtitle":"Thread Communication simulation","prevslug":"/thread-communication-simulation"}}}